Sheet1.Description: Position yourself on a glute-ham raise machine with your feet secured. Lower your upper body towards the floor, then raise it back up by contracting your hamstrings.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lift the barbell from the floor to your shoulders (clean), then press it overhead. Lower it back to your shoulders and then to the floor.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lift the barbell from the floor to an overhead position in one explosive motion. Lower it back to the floor with control.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lower your body by bending your knees forward while keeping your torso upright. Return to the starting position.
Stand on one leg and squat down, keeping your other leg extended in front of you. Return to the starting position.
Stand on one leg and lower your body into a squat while keeping the other leg extended in front of you. Return to the starting position.
Kick up into a handstand position against a wall. Lower your head towards the ground by bending your elbows, then push back up.
Perform deep squats holding a barbell across your shoulders.
Perform dips with added weight using a dip belt.
Alternate between plank and push-up positions.
Perform presses on an incline bench to target the upper chest.
Rest one foot on a bench and squat with the other leg.
Extend your legs against resistance to isolate the quadriceps.
Lift the barbell from the ground by extending through the hips and knees.
Pull a dumbbell towards your hip while supporting yourself with the other arm.
Perform pull-ups with added weight using a dip belt.
Swing the kettlebell between your legs and up to chest height.
Lie on your back and lift your legs and torso while keeping your shoulders on the ground.
Perform deadlifts standing on an elevated platform to increase range.
Push up while extending one arm out to the side for a greater challenge.
Lie on a bench and open your arms wide with dumbbells.
Kneel and lower your body forward while keeping your knees on the floor.
